{"type":"message","id":"1a8527e7","parentId":"d3bbc928","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:25:04.896Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so yfinance itself is logging at level 0 (NOTSET) which means it propagates to root, and root has `level=logging.INFO` via basicConfig. So yfinance messages go to the same log file.\n\nNow I need to find the specific yfinance ERROR messages in the log. Let me look at the actual log entries more carefully. The error pattern was:\n```\n2026-05-12 14:47:03,188 [ERROR] \n1 Failed download:\n2026-05-12 14:47:03,188 [ERROR] ['EX443']: possibly delisted; no timezone found\n\n\n```\n\nThis is the yfinance logger, not ray_backtest_630.py's own logging. So I need to fix this by adding `encoding='utf-8'` to basicConfig and silencing yfinance.ERROR level messages for known benign cases like delisted symbols.\n\nFor P0, I'll add encoding and filter out delisted messages. For P1, the encoding is already there in the other scripts. For P2, feedparser is actually installed—the issue is that the Yahoo RSS feed is returning 0 entries. For P3, Jina is returning 403 errors. Let me check if the EX* symbols in the 630 script are the source of the problem, then figure out why Yahoo RSS returns nothing.\n\n```\n","thinkingSignature":"06e4cdb1b347d9d766953e292f3a0a9955fbbd7a32f61064e5edaa30aeaf6d87"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r2890eemlpoj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport re\nc = open(r'C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\ray_backtest_630.py', encoding='utf-8', errors='ignore').read()\n# Find the EX generation code and the main loop\n# Check how skipped symbols are counted\nidx = c.find('skipped += 1')\nprint('Context around skipped:')\nprint(c[max(0,idx-200):idx+100])\n\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":115,"output":407,"cacheRead":129472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129994,"cost":{"input":0.0000345,"outpu