{"type":"message","id":"fba3fc21","parentId":"939e0b91","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:26:01.129Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found it. Line 117-120:\n\n```python\n# 如果不足 630，補充備用\nif len(all_tickers) < 630:\n    extras = [f\"EX{i}\" for i in range(630 - len(all_tickers))]\n    all_tickers.extend(extras)\n```\n\nSo the script generates fake symbols like `EX0`, `EX1`, ..., `EX466` (if there are only ~164 real tickers found) to fill up to 630. Then `backtest_symbol()` is called on all of them, and for the fake EX symbols, yfinance will fail with \"possibly delisted\" - but these are logged by yfinance's internal logger, not by the script's `_log`.\n\n\nNow I need to fix this by suppressing yfinance's logger, setting encoding to utf-8 in basicConfig, and stopping the EX symbol generation. Let me examine the full file structure to understand how the main function works.\n","thinkingSignature":"6ac6f070a074c2071b7a8931a25195c600082c7279f643cebd38317b97b059a3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ltxgf0dnjb33_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":40,"offset":195,"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\ray_backtest_630.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2300,"output":261,"cacheRead":130240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132801,"cost":{"input":0.00069,"output":0.00031319999999999997,"cacheRead":0.007814399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008817599999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778588755243,"responseId":"06524f557e509240762f13a7defc6003"}}
{"type":"message","id":"547ea2eb","parentId":"fba3fc21","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:26:01.135Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ltxgf0dnjb33_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        return None\n\n# ============================================================\n# 主程序\n# ============================================================\ndef run_630_backtest():\n    _log.info(\"=== 630 檔回測啟動 ===\")\n\n    symbols = get_symbol_list()\n    print(f\"總計: {len(symbols)} 檔\")\n    print()\n\n    today = time.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(DB)\n    c = conn.cursor()\n\n    written = 0\n    skipped = 0\n\n    print(\"開始回測...\")\n    for i, symbol in enumerate(symbols):\n        if (i + 1) % 50 == 0:\n            print(f\"  進度: {i+1}/{len(symbols)} ({written} 筆寫入)\")\n\n        results = backtest_symbol(symbol)\n        if results:\n            for r in results:\n                if r[\"sharpe\"] > 0:  # 只寫入正 Sharpe\n                    c.execute(f'''INSERT INTO backtest_reports\n                        (timestamp, strategy_name, symbol, indicator, params, sharpe_ratio, max_drawdown, total_return, win_rate, avg_return, num_trades, passed, note)\n                        VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)''',\n                        (today, r[\"strategy\"], symbol, r[\"indicator\"],\n                         json.dumps({\"ma20\": True, \"rsi_max\": 70}),\n                         round(r[\"sharpe\"], 2), round(r[\"mdd\"], 2), round(r[\"ret\"], 2),\n                         round(r[\"win\"], 1), round(r[\"ret\"] / max(r[\"trades\"], 1), 3),\n                         r[\"trades\"], 1 if r[\"sharpe\"] >= 1.5 else 0,\n                         f\"630 回測\"))\n                    written += 1\n        else:\n            skipped += 1\n\n[27 more lines in file. Use offset=235 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778588761134}}
{"type":"message","id":"81f80dcc","parentId":"547ea2eb","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:26:12.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ray_backtest_630.py file doesn't explicitly log ERROR for delisted symbols. The 97KB of ERROR messages must come from yfinance's internal logging. \n\nLooking at the file structure:\n1. `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)` at line 19 - sets root logger to INFO\n2. But `basicConfig` only applies if no handlers exist on the root logger\n3. Once basicConfig sets the root logger, yfinance also propagates to root\n\nThe fix: Add `handlers=[]` to basicConfig to prevent yfinance from adding its own handlers, OR suppress yfinance logger before basicConfig.\n\nAlso the logging has no `encoding='utf-8'` in basicConfig.\n\n\nThe 97KB flood is coming from yfinance outputting ERROR logs for all those EX symbols, and since the root logger is set to INFO level with a file handler pointing to ray_backtest_630.log, those ERROR messages are getting written there. The core issues are that yfinance's own logging is producing the errors and basicConfig is missing the encoding parameter.\n","thinkingSignature":"76f7a27825f33d7a2d5b4cd2caafa8c82827c8efad714ab45148206d3f7cf752"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3pyg5hj76141_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport logging, yfinance as yf, io, sys\n\n# Capture yfinance ERROR logs\nold_stderr = sys.stderr\nsys.stderr = io.StringIO()\n\n# Create log capture\nimport logging\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG, format='%(name)s [%(levelname)s] %(message)s')\nyh = logging.getLogger('yfinance')\n\n# Now run a delisted symbol to see what happens\ntry:\n    yf.download('EX999', progress=False, timeout=5)\nexcept:\n    pass\n\ncaptured = sys.stderr.getvalue()\nsys.stderr = old_stderr\nprint('Captured stderr:', repr(captured[:200]) if captured else 'None')\n\n# Check yfinance logger\nprint('yfinance logger level:', yh.level)\nprint('yfinance handlers:', yh.handlers)\nprint('yfinance propagate:', yh.propagate)\n\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":550,"output":436,"cacheRead":132480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133466,"cost":{"input":0.000165,"output":0.0005231999999999999,"cacheRead":0.007948799999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008636999999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778588761140,"responseId":"06524f5b1afd7cccd39466ffe9cd2acb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"dbac2c67","parentId":"81f80dcc","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:26:16.233Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3pyg5hj76141_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Captured stderr: 'yfinance [DEBUG] Entering download()\\nyfinance [DEBUG] Disabling multithreading because DEBUG logging enabled\\nyfinance [DEBUG]  Entering history()\\npeewee [DEBUG] (\\'CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS \"_tz_kv\" ('\r\nyfinance logger level: 0\r\nyfinance handlers: []\r\nyfinance propagate: True"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4205,"aggregated":"Captured stderr: 'yfinance [DEBUG] Entering download()\\nyfinance [DEBUG] Disabling multithreading because DEBUG logging enabled\\nyfinance [DEBUG]  Entering history()\\npeewee [DEBUG] (\\'CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS \"_tz_kv\" ('\r\nyfinance logger level: 0\r\nyfinance handlers: []\r\nyfinance propagate: True","cwd":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778588776233}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a7f7226","parentId":"dbac2c67","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:26:37.799Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the yfinance ERROR logs come from peewee (SQLite internal) or yfinance itself, not from the Python stderr but from the logging system. The root logger is configured to write to a file (ray_backtest_630.log). So all logs (yfinance, peewee, etc.) that propagate to root go to that file.\n\nThe 97KB log is mostly yfinance and peewee DEBUG logs, plus yfinance ERROR logs for delisted symbols. The solution is:\n\n1. Suppress yfinance logging to ERROR only (or WARNING)\n2. Add `encoding='utf-8'` to basicConfig\n\n\n3. Filter out the \"possibly delisted\" errors so they don't clutter the log\n\nI'll fix the logging configuration in ray_backtest_630.py now.\n","thinkingSignature":"04ecd3e1ac2b8d1b8d09c28366a04aae235c7bb5c62c2413b28f5ce2561140c8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bmxdj7ztlpjj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\n# Verify yfinance ERROR for delisted symbol goes to log\nimport logging, sys, io\n\n# Capture to check what's logged\nold = sys.stderr\nsys.stderr = io.StringIO()\n\n# Configure minimal logging\nlogging.basicConfig(\n    level=logging.INFO,\n    format='%(name)s [%(levelname)s] %(message)s'\n)\n\n# Suppress yfinance DEBUG\nyf_l = logging.getLogger('yfinance')\nyf_l.setLevel(logging.WARNING)\n\ntry:\n    import yfinance as yf\n    yf.download('EX999', progress=False, timeout=5)\nexcept:\n    pass\n\ncaptured = sys.stderr.getvalue()\nsys.stderr = old\n# Count lines\nlines = captured.strip().split(chr(10))\nprint(f'Lines: {len(lines)}')\nfor l in lines[:5]:\n    print(repr(l[:100]))\n\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":349,"output":377,"cacheRead":132992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133718,"cost":{"input":0.0001047,"output":0.0004524,"cacheRead":0.007979519999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008