{"type":"message","id":"32ecd1ac","parentId":"8a7f7226","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:26:41.271Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bmxdj7ztlpjj_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Lines: 5\r\n'yfinance [ERROR] HTTP Error 404: {\"quoteSummary\":{\"result\":null,\"error\":{\"code\":\"Not Found\",\"descrip'\r\n'yfinance [ERROR] $EX999: possibly delisted; no price data found  (period=1mo) (Yahoo error = \"No dat'\r\n'yfinance [ERROR] '\r\n'1 Failed download:'\r\n'yfinance [ERROR] [\\'EX999\\']: possibly delisted; no price data found  (period=1mo) (Yahoo error = \"No '"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3465,"aggregated":"Lines: 5\r\n'yfinance [ERROR] HTTP Error 404: {\"quoteSummary\":{\"result\":null,\"error\":{\"code\":\"Not Found\",\"descrip'\r\n'yfinance [ERROR] $EX999: possibly delisted; no price data found  (period=1mo) (Yahoo error = \"No dat'\r\n'yfinance [ERROR] '\r\n'1 Failed download:'\r\n'yfinance [ERROR] [\\'EX999\\']: possibly delisted; no price data found  (period=1mo) (Yahoo error = \"No '","cwd":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778588801271}}
{"type":"message","id":"99a2098d","parentId":"32ecd1ac","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:26:56.063Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The yfinance ERROR comes from yfinance's own logger (`logging.getLogger('yfinance')`), and when `logging.basicConfig()` is called with `level=logging.INFO`, yfinance's ERROR messages (which are at ERROR level = 30) get printed to stderr.\n\nThe yfinance logger has `propagate=True` by default, so its ERROR messages bubble up to the root logger. Since `basicConfig` sets up the root logger with a StreamHandler (to stderr), the ERROR messages appear in stderr.\n\nBut wait - in the actual script, `logging.basicConfig(filename=...)` only sets up a FileHandler, not a StreamHandler. So yfinance's ERROR messages should NOT appear in the file... unless there's a StreamHandler somewhere.\n \nActually, `logging.basicConfig(filename=...)` creates a FileHandler on the root logger, but yfinance's ERROR messages propagate up and get caught by that FileHandler. The solution is to set `yf_l.setLevel(logging.WARNING + 1)` before the basicConfig call so yfinance's ERROR messages don't get captured. Alternatively, I could add `force=True` to the basicConfig call to ensure it doesn't get called multiple times, or just add the yfinance suppression as a safeguard.\n\nNow I'm going to apply these fixes: add yfinance ERROR suppression before basicConfig, set up a proper FileHandler with UTF-8 encoding, and avoid basicConfig so I can control the logger configuration more precisely.\n","thinkingSignature":"221f6a92742d08b555f163f39526fe68b4feedb9dd7df2c43f756606b8ecf44f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到了！**yfinance 的 ERROR logger 是 flood 來源**。`logging.basicConfig(filename=...)` 註冊到 root logger，yfinance 的 ERROR 等級（30）>= INFO（20），所以全部被寫入 log 檔。\n\n現在立即修改：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_eoegq1v9guqv_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"import sys, sqlite3, json, time, logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8', errors='replace')\n\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom concurrent.futures import ThreadPoolExecutor, as_completed\n\nDB = 'ray_wisdom.db'\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\nLOG_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n\n# ── 抑制 yfinance ERROR flood（已下市符號不重要）───\nyf_logger = logging.getLogger('yfinance')\nyf_logger.setLevel(logging.WARNING + 1)  # 只有 WARNING 以上才記錄，ERROR 安靜跳過\n\n# ── 設定 FileHandler（明確指定 UTF-8）───\n_log = logging.getLogger(\"backtest_630\")\n_log.setLevel(logging.INFO)\n_fh = logging.FileHandler(str(LOG_DIR / \"ray_backtest_630.log\"), encoding='utf-8')\n_fh.setFormatter(logging.Formatter('%(asctime)s [%(levelname)s] %(message)s'))\n_log.addHandler(_fh)\n_log.propagate = False  # 不向上傳播，避免root handler重複","oldText":"import sys, sqlite3, json, time, logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8', errors='replace')\n\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom concurrent.futures import ThreadPoolExecutor, as_completed\n\nDB = 'ray_wisdom.db'\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\nLOG_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n\nlogging.basicConfig(\n    filename=str(LOG_DIR / \"ray_backtest_630.log\"),\n    level=logging.INFO,\n    format=\"%(asctime)s [%(levelname)s] %(message)s\"\n)\n_log = logging.getLogger(\"backtest_630\")"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\ray_backtest_630.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":373,"output":857,"cacheRead":133312,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134542,"cost":{"input":0.0001119,"output":0.0010284,"cacheRead":0.007998719999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00913902}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778588801276,"responseId":"06524f82357a9d15550b71cf76c2f68a"}}
