{"type":"message","id":"51acbf35","parentId":"021330a4","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:35:32.661Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me analyze:\n\n- `wisdom_corrections`: 63 total\n  - UNKNOWN: 14 (not yet labeled)\n  - VEA: 11 (mostly from backtest)\n  - BND: 9\n  - GLD: 8\n  - SPY: 7\n  - DEEP: 3 (from deep analysis)\n  - WEB_SOURCE: 1 (only 1 record from web learning!)\n\nThe `wisdom_logs`: 360 entries but most have `passed=0` (failed).\n\nThe web learning is basically not working. Only 1 WEB_SOURCE record.\n\nKey issues:\n\n\nThe system is generating very few actual insights through its web learning pipeline. Looking at the architecture, there's a bottleneck where `validate_with_7b` is supposed to write validated insights to the database, but it's only creating a single record. The flow goes from Tavily fetching articles through filtering, gate checks, validation with MiniMax, and then writing - but most articles are being filtered out or failing validation before they reach the database.\n\nThe core problem seems to be that the system's self-correction loop is actually producing fewer corrections than expected, and the web learning component isn't functioning properly to compensate for this gap.\n","thinkingSignature":"4d5b72ff570699624e79b2a037e7fe76454ff5e3ff97b916952f532b57923425"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hlo7c4adkxt6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import sqlite3; conn=sqlite3.connect(r'C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\ray_wisdom.db'); c=conn.cursor(); c.execute('SELECT COUNT(*) FROM wisdom_logs WHERE passed=0'); failed=c.fetchone()[0]; c.execute('SELECT COUNT(*) FROM wisdom_logs'); total=c.fetchone()[0]; c.execute('SELECT COUNT(*) FROM wisdom_logs WHERE passed=1'); passed=c.fetchone()[0]; print(f'wisdom_logs: total={total}, passed={passed}, failed={failed}'); conn.close()\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":