{"type":"message","id":"0c4c627a","parentId":"f8df1e0e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:38:23.753Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fbv5qz1v1lrv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def jina_read_convert(url):\r\n    \"\"\"DEPRECATED: Use fetch_tavily_articles instead\"\"\"\r\n    return None\r\n\r\ndef fetch_tavily_articles(queries, max_results=5):\r\n    \"\"\"用 Tavily 搜尋取代 Jina Reader（更穩定）\"\"\"\r\n    articles = []\r\n    try:\r\n        import requests\r\n        for q in queries:\r\n            try:\r\n                resp = requests.post(\r\n                    \"https://api.tavily.com/search\",\r\n                    json={\"query\": q, \"api_key\": TAVILY_KEY, \"max_results\": max_results, \"topic\": \"finance\"},\r\n                    timeout=15\r\n                )\r\n                if resp.status_code == 200:\r\n                    for r in resp.json().get(\"results\", [])[:3]:\r\n                        content = r.get(\"content\", \"\")[:500]\r\n                        if is_relevant(content):\r\n                            articles.append({\r\n                                \"title\": r.get(\"title\", \"\")[:100],\r\n                                \"summary\": content,\r\n                                \"url\": r.get(\"url\", \"\")\r\n                            })\r\n            except Exception as e:\r\n                _log.warning(f\"Tavily query failed: {e}\")\r\n    except ImportError:\r\n        pass\r\n    return articles\r\n\r\n# ============================================================\r\n# 2. 關鍵詞預選（直接捨棄無關內容）\r\n# ============================================================\r\n\r\n\n[207 more lines in file. Use offset=113 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778589503753}}
{"type":"message","id":"dd8a7ea1","parentId":"0c4c627a","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:38:34.500Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue! `fetch_tavily_articles` is defined before `is_relevant`. But in the file, `is_relevant` is defined after the function, so when `fetch_tavily_articles` calls `is_relevant()` at line 97, `is_relevant` doesn't exist yet! That's the bug.\n\nWait, but Python functions are compiled at definition time, and when called at runtime, `is_relevant` should be defined... unless the function is called before the module finishes loading.\n\nActually in Python this should work because `is_relevant` is defined by the time the function is called (runtime). The function body is only evaluated when called, not when defined. So `is_relevant` should exist by then.\n \nThe test script works because it's calling `is_relevant` directly in the same scope where it's defined. But in the module, `fetch_tavily_articles` is being called from the main loop before `is_relevant` is actually defined in that module's namespace. That's the real issue—Python's closure mechanism can't resolve the reference when the function is called too early.\n","thinkingSignature":"67ac5de0708d2c4b08f5dfc1900799cd3d994ed0f1980a529ad779bc48622b96"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yyxdxozfm81s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, r'C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray')\n# Test if is_relevant is defined when fetch_tavily_articles runs\nimport ray_econ_learner as m\nprint('is_relevant:', hasattr(m, 'is_relevant'))\nprint('fetch_tavily_articles:', hasattr(m, 'fetch_tavily_articles'))\nprint('TAVILY_KEY:', m.TAVILY_KEY[:20] + '...')\n\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":392,"output":376,"cacheRead":155136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":155904,"cost":{"input":0.0001176,"output":0.00045119999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0093