{"type":"message","id":"1effec5a","parentId":"8cdbcd38","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:41:39.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The script runs but returns 0 articles. The issue must be in `fetch_tavily_articles()`. Let me add a print statement directly in the `ray_econ_learner.py` file to debug.Actually, let me think about this differently. The standalone test worked. The module test returned [].\n\nWait - when I ran the debug test I wrote earlier (debug_tavily.py), it produced no output. But when I ran the inline Python one-liner test, it worked fine. The difference?\n\nIn debug_tavily.py, I defined `is_relevant` BEFORE calling `fetch_tavily_articles`. In ray_econ_learner.py, `fetch_tavily_articles` is defined at line ~82 and `is_relevant` is defined at line ~113.Let me check if maybe `is_relevant` in the module is somehow different from what I think. \n\nActually, I should just add some print statements directly into the `fetch_tavily_articles()` function in ray_econ_learner.py to see what's actually happening when it runs.","thinkingSignature":"2d77fb3dcc706000e166e972883a9945c5b2f9b1c710164ba80006446080c12f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hy1l9o4xp2og_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"def fetch_tavily_articles(queries, max_results=5):\n    \"\"\"用 Tavily 搜尋取代 Jina Reader（更穩定）\"\"\"\n    import sys\n    print(\"DEBUG: fetch_tavily_articles called\", flush=True)\n    articles = []\n    for q in queries:\n        try:\n            import requests\n            resp = requests.post(\n                \"https://api.tavily.com/search\",\n                json={\"query\": q, \"api_key\": TAVILY_KEY, \"max_results\": max_results, \"topic\": \"finance\"},\n                timeout=15\n            )\n            print(f\"DEBUG: query={q}, status={resp.status_code}\", flush=True)\n            if resp.status_code == 200:\n                results = resp.json().get(\"results\", [])[:3]\n                print(f\"DEBUG: {len(results)} results for {q}\", flush=True)\n                for r in results:\n                    content = r.get(\"content\", \"\")[:500]\n                    print(f\"DEBUG: checking relevance for: {r.get('title','')[:40]}\", flush=True)\n                    rel = is_relevant(content)\n                    print(f\"DEBUG: is_relevant={rel}\", flush=True)\n                    if rel:\n                        articles.append({\n                            \"title\": r.get(\"title\", \"\")[:100],\n                            \"summary\": content,\n                            \"url\": r.get(\"url\", \"\")\n                        })\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"DEBUG: exception: {e}\", flush=True)\n            _log.warning(f\"Tavily query failed: {e}\")\n    print(f\"DEBUG: returning {len(articles)} articles\", flush=True)\n    return articles","oldText":"def fetch_tavily_articles(queries, max_results=5):\n    \"\"\"用 Tavily 搜尋取代 Jina Reader（更穩定）\"\"\"\n    articles = []\n    try:\n        import requests\n        for q in queries:\n            try:\n                resp = requests.post(\n                    \"https://api.tavily.com/search\",\n                    json={\"query\": q, \"api_key\": TAVILY_KEY, \"max_results\": max_results, \"topic\": \"finance\"},\n                    timeout=15\n                )\n                if resp.status_code == 200:\n                    for r in resp.json().get(\"results\", [])[:3]:\n                        content = r.get(\"content\", \"\")[:500]\n                        if is_relevant(content):\n                            articles.append({\n                                \"title\": r.get(\"title\", \"\")[:100],\n                                \"summary\": content,\n                                \"url\": r.get(\"url\", \"\")\n                            })\n            except Exception as e:\n                _log.warning(f\"Tavily query failed: {e}\")\n    except ImportError:\n        pass\n    return articles"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\ray_econ_learner.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23678,"output":956,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40383,"cost":{"input":0.007103399999999999,"output":0.0011472,"cacheRead":0.0009449399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009195539999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778589680332,"responseId":"065252f1bfa1af944eff6fbbcbe1ba3f"}}
