{"type":"message","id":"41fa555d","parentId":"21a7b313","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:43:36.937Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The total WEB_SOURCE in the DB is 3. This means:\n- econ_learner added 3 records (its run showed 3)\n- web_learner's run (which showed \"總 web_source: 3 筆\") - wait, but it ran after econ_learner and showed 3 total. If it wrote new ones, the total should be more than 3.\n\nActually wait - web_learner ran AFTER econ_learner and got 3 total. But econ_learner had already written 3. So web_learner's 10 filtered articles must have failed the LLM gate check and wrote 0. The \"總 web_source: 3 筆\" is just the existing count + new writes from this run = 3 total.\n \nSo the economy learner's working correctly with Tavily returning 10 relevant articles and producing 3 rules, while the web learner's working too but hitting the LLM gate with 10 articles in and 0 passing through - I need to investigate why that gate is so strict. Let me check what's currently in the database.","thinkingSignature":"2a232db1998cb40bf5e46f28030d90b0f30b70a47cd159431c671d96292f2029"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gp5zhzvjl426_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import sqlite3; conn=sqlite3.connect(r'C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\ray_wisdom.db'); c=conn.cursor(); c.execute('SELECT id, created_at, diagnosis, confidence FROM wisdom_corrections WHERE symbol=? ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT 5',('WEB_SOURCE',)); [print(r) for r in c.fetchall()]; conn.close()\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":27388,"output":348,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43485,"cost":{"input":0.0082164,"output":0.00041759999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0009449399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009578940000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778589805900,"responseId":"0652536f10f1ccbee90f3dba1183f06f"}}
