{"type":"message","id":"303e4f8f","parentId":"656a6385","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:49:34.460Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to run `ollama create ray-v3 -f ray-v3.Modelfile`. But wait - the FROM line says `ray-v3:latest`, and I'm creating `ray-v3.Modelfile`. This will cause a circular reference! \n\nThe Modelfile needs to be created with a different name or I need to use `FROM qwen3.5:4b` directly since that's the actual base model.\n\nLet me check: `ollama list` showed `ray-v3:latest` as the model. This means `ray-v3` is already a model in Ollama created from a previous Modelfile. \n\nI should create the Modelfile under a new name like `ray-v3-commander` and use `FROM qwen3.5:4b` as the base, then run `ollama create ray-v3-commander -f ray-v3-commander.Modelfile` to avoid the circular reference.\n\nActually, since `ray-v3` is already registered in Ollama from a previous base, I can just update its Modelfile directly and recreate it with `ollama create ray-v3 -f ray-v3.Modelfile`. I need to be careful about the FROM instruction though—if the Modelfile specifies `FROM ray-v3:latest`, Ollama will use whatever blob is already cached for that tag, so I should verify what the original Modelfile actually contained.\n\nSince Jo specifically requested naming the file `ray-v3.Modelfile` and using `ollama create` to update the existing `ray-v3` model, I'll go with that approach and create the Modelfile to reference the base model, then recreate it.","thinkingSignature":"1c6ba091db9f9a771316cf6d1e8d7659a99ddda0dad259c31867b8d765d25efa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zc9r8y6b13l9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray && ollama create ray-v3 -f ray-v3.Modelfile 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36015,"output":415,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52179,"cost":{"input":0.0108045,"outpu