{"type":"message","id":"64734fa3","parentId":"8ce36094","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:51:46.688Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Modelfile has invalid syntax. The issue is that comments using `###` are not valid Modelfile syntax. In Ollama Modelfiles:\n- Comments should use `#` but not `###` as a section delimiter\n- The valid syntax is `FROM`, `PARAMETER`, `SYSTEM`, `MESSAGE`, etc.\n\nLet me look at an existing Modelfile to understand the correct syntax.","thinkingSignature":"b128708693f9d99a3e774575f3c7f93c0aaa801a694e1c00070e71c8934d8c23"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hd6g5kz9hax8_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\ray-deep-v1.Modelfile"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36826,"output":129,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52704,"cost":{"input":0.0110478,"output":0.0001548,"cacheRead":0.0009449399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01214754}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778590183579,"responseId":"0652555a93e7316bbb4301a83ec27467"}}
{"type":"message","id":"350a76da","parentId":"64734fa3","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:51:46.699Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hd6g5kz9hax8_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"FROM qwen2.5:7b\n\n# Ray Deep Brain (參謀總長) - 深度歸因分析\n# 用途：盤後深度反思、策略歸因、邏輯修正、蒸餾教練\n\nPARAMETER num_ctx 8192\nPARAMETER temperature 0.3\nPARAMETER top_p 0.85\nPARAMETER num_gpu 1\n\nSYSTEM \"\"\"\nYou are Ray-Deep (Qwen 7B), the Chief Strategist of the Tina Quant System.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n1. Post-market deep reflection on failed trades\n2. Strategy attribution analysis\n3. Logic correction for failed axioms\n4. Mentor for distillation (teaching 1.5B student)\n\nYour outputs MUST be valid JSON. No natural language unless asked.\nSchema for analysis: {\"diagnosis\":\"...\", \"corrected_axiom\":{...}, \"confidence\":0.0-1.0, \"master_reference\":\"...\"}\n\nYou have access to:\n- 16k context window (use it fully for deep analysis)\n- Market regime knowledge (Simons/Momentum regime switching)\n- Connors RSI mean reversion logic\n- Aronson's evidence-based validation\n- Prado's meta-labeling framework\n\nThink deeply. Output precisely.\n\"\"\""}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778590306699}}
{"type":"message","id":"798bbd46","parentId":"350a76da","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:52:01.507Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the correct Modelfile syntax. The system prompt goes in a `SYSTEM \"\"\"...\"\"\"` block. Let me rewrite the ray-v3.Modelfile correctly.\n\nAlso, I need to use `FROM qwen3.5:4b` (or the actual base model name) rather than `ray-v3:latest` to avoid circular reference.\n\nBut wait - the Ollama model list shows `ray-v3:latest` with size 3.4GB. This means it was created from some base (probably `qwen3.5:4b` or similar). Let me check what the original ray-v3 Modelfile looked like, if any.","thinkingSignature":"3afb644d0c7f7ef7640cf568429f3000919cce0d306cfd9fb10951898fae3d02"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tasv28b8ktf5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ollama show ray-v3 --modelfile 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37230,"output":187,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53166,"cost":{"input":0.011169,"output":0.00022439999999999998,"cacheRead":0.0009449399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01233834}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778590306702,"responseId":"065255632862ba88c5e79094eaf306f2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bdfea5c1","parentId":"798bbd46","timestamp":"2026-05-12T12:52:02.200Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tasv28b8ktf5_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Modelfile generated by \"ollama show\"\n# To build a new Modelfile based on this, replace FROM with:\n# FROM ray-v3:latest\n\nFROM C:\\Users\\USER\\.ollama\\models\\blobs\\sha256-81fb60c7daa80fc1123380b98970b320ae233409f0f71a72ed7b9b0d62f40490\nTEMPLATE {{ .Prompt }}\nSYSTEM \"\n你是 Ray，Jo 的專屬美股/ETF 自動交易 Agent。不是 Tina。\n風格：簡單、直接、執行導向。Emoji：📈\n\n== 身份 ==\nName: Ray\nRole: 美股 ETF 自動交易 Agent + Qwen 本地大腦協調者\nFocus: VTI/VOO/QQQ/BND/VEA DCA、美股趨勢追蹤、美股波段操作\n\n== 決策原則 ==\n1. 執行優先：討論確定了就執行，不拖延\n2. 風險第一：任何交易先確認停損\n3. 透明誠實：失敗了立刻承認，不找藉口\n\n== 風險門檻系統（2026-05-12 重構）==\n\n加倉美股需同時滿足（Green Zone）：\n1. TWII RSI < 80（必要非充分條件）\n2. VIX < 25（市場情緒穩定）\n3. WTI 原油 < 95（排除通膨失控）\n4. 目標標的 RSI < 75（個股自己不能太貴）\n5. 美股趨勢向上（MA20 > MA60）\n\n任一條件滿足則禁加倉（Red Zone）：\n- VIX > 25（市場恐慌）\n- TWII RSI > 90（台股明顯過熱）\n- WTI 原油 > 100（原物料通膨失控）\n- 標的 RSI > 80（自己已經超買）\n\n信號燈系統：\n| 指標 | Red Zone | Yellow Zone | Green Zone |\n|------|---------|-------------|------------|\n| TWII RSI | > 90 | 80-90 | < 80 |\n| VIX | > 25 | 20-25 | < 20 |\n| WTI 原油 | > 100 | 90-100 | < 90 |\n| 個股 RSI | > 80 | 70-80 | < 70 |\n\n核心邏輯：\n- VIX 是核心指標（系統性風險）\n- 個股 RSI > 80 才是進場紀律核心問題\n- 台股過熱 → 預警 TSM ADR 連動風險，絕非直接禁買美股\n\n== 資料庫（ray_wisdom.db）==\n\nSQLite WAL 模式，並發安全\n- backtest_reports: 1057筆, Avg Sharpe 1.43, Max 7.52\n- wisdom_logs: 360筆\n- wisdom_corrections: 63筆（高信心22筆）\n- signals_log: 15筆\n- daily_performance: 28筆\n- trades_log: 1筆（Demo trade，VOO DCA）\n\n== 回測引擎標準 ==\n\n- 摩擦成本：0.15%（美股）\n- Sharpe > 1.5（高質量策略）\n- MDD < 15%（風險控制）\n- Win Rate > 45%\n\n== 主要策略 ==\n\n策略候選人（Grid）：\n- EMA_CROSS（9/21, 12/26, 20/60, 50/200）\n- MOMENTUM（5, 20, 60日）\n- VEGAS_TUNNEL（144/576, 169/676）\n- RSI_THRESHOLD（RSI2 < 30 超賣）\n- KDJ_CROSS（period=9, 穿越20）\n\n== 禁止事項 ==\n\n- 未經 Jo 確認就下單\n- 忽略停損紀律\n- 在 Red Zone 條件下加倉美股\n\n== Ollama 模型 ==\n\n- ray-v1: 986MB（Qwen 1.5B，快速策略提案）\n- ray-deep-v1: 4.7GB（Qwen 7B，深度推理）\n- qwen2.5:7b: 4.7GB（備用）\n- qwen3.5:4b: 3.4GB（思考模式）\n\n== 數據來源 ==\n\n- Yahoo Finance（yfinance）：美股/ETF歷史數據\n- FinMind：台股基本面\n- Tavily：即時新聞情緒\n- Yahoo Finance 即時：TWII、VIX、原油\n\n== 波段操作標的 ==\n\n重點：NVDA、TSLA、META、MSFT、AAPL、QCOM、AMD、AVGO、MU、INTC\nETF：VTI、VOO、QQQ、BND、VEA、GLD\n\"\nRENDERER qwen3.5\nPARSER qwen3.5\nPARAMETER temperature 1\nPARAMETER top_k 20\nPARAMETER top_p 0.95\nPARAMETER presence_penalty 1.5\nLICENSE \"\"\"                                Apache License\n                           Version 2.0, January 2004\n                        http://www.apache.org/licenses/\n\n   TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR USE, REPRODUCTION, AND DISTRIBUTION\n\n   1. Definitions.\n\n      \"License\" shall mean the terms and conditions for use, reproduction,\n      and distribution as defined by Sections 1 through 9 of this document.\n\n      \"Licensor\" shall mean the copyright owner or entity authorized by\n      the copyright owner that is granting the License.\n\n      \"Legal Entity\" shall mean the union of the acting entity and all\n      other entities that control, are controlled by, or are under common\n      control with that entity. For the purposes of this definition,\n      \"control\" means (i) the power, direct or indirect, to cause the\n      direction or management of such entity, whether by contract or\n      otherwise, or (ii) ownership of fifty percent (50%) or more of the\n      outstanding shares, or (iii) beneficial ownership of such entity.\n\n      \"You\" (or \"Your\") shall mean an individual or Legal Entity\n      exercising permissions granted by this License.\n\n      \"Source\" form shall mean the preferred form for making modifications,\n      including but not limited to software source code, documentation\n      source, and configuration files.\n\n      \"Object\" form shall mean any form resulting from mechanical\n      transformation or translation of a Source form, including but\n      