{"type":"message","id":"137365e4","parentId":"5a02fc72","timestamp":"2026-05-12T13:01:28.930Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The process was killed (SIGKILL). This means ray-v3 is hanging when run with `ollama run`. This could be because the model is loading but takes too long, or there's an issue with the way the model is configured.\n\nLet me check the `ollama run` behavior with a simpler model.Actually, looking at this more carefully, the issue might be that `ollama run` is interactive and waiting for input. Let me try with the API directly using a longer timeout.\n\nActually, let me step back. The test showed:\n- `v3_commander()` in the router returned in 5.6s but with empty content\n- Direct ollama API call also timed out at 30s\n\n\n- `ollama run` with ray-v3 was killed after 60s\n\nThis suggests ray-v3 is either extremely slow to respond or hanging entirely. Let me test with ray-v1 which was working before to see if the API itself is responsive.","thinkingSignature":"542b9770b52d80796d02e26cc3e0e7f36a6a0f68bfcb2b249e27be24ec62b1d6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yslf70xtcjdm_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_api_quick.py","content":"\"\"\"Test Ollama API with quick model\"\"\"\nimport urllib.request, json, time\n\n# Test with ray-v1 first (known to work fast)\npayload = {\n    \"model\": \"ray-v1\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Say 'test' in one word only.\"}],\n    \"stream\": False\n}\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    \"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\",\n    data=json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\"),\n    headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    method=\"POST\"\n)\nprint(\"Testing ray-v1...\")\nstart = time.time()\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=15) as resp:\n        raw = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n        print(f\"ray-v1 OK ({time.time()-start:.1f}s):\", raw.get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")[:50])\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"ray-v1 FAIL: {e}\")\n\n# Test with ray-v3\npayload2 = {\n    \"model\": \"ray-v3\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Say 'test' in one word only.\"}],\n    \"stream\": False,\n    \"options\": {\"temperature\": 0.1}\n}\nreq2 = urllib.request.Request(\n    \"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\",\n    data=json.dumps(payload2).encode(\"utf-8\"),\n    headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    method=\"POST\"\n)\nprint(\"\\nTesting ray-v3...\")\nstart = time.time()\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req2, timeout=20) as resp:\n        raw = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n        content = raw.get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n        print(f\"ray-v3 OK ({time.time()-start:.1f}s): {content[:100]}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"ray-v3 FAIL after {time.time()-start:.1f}s: {e}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54681,"output":692,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71122,"cost":{"input":0.0164043,"output":0.0008303999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0009449399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.018179639999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778590872295,"responseId":"0652579a7f7060e8301c08d0189cd6aa"}}
