{"type":"message","id":"a50ec12f","parentId":"d5aeb064","timestamp":"2026-05-12T13:03:01.444Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `ray-v1` works fine (6.3s) but `ray-v3` times out at 22s. This is a problem - `ray-v3` (qwen3.5:4b, 3.4GB) is extremely slow or hanging.\n\nThe issue is likely that:\n1. `ray-v3` is configured without proper template/prompt handling in the Modelfile\n2. The model might be waiting for more input due to the template format\n\nLet me check what the Modelfile's TEMPLATE does. In my Modelfile:\n```\nTEMPLATE \"\"\"\n{{ if .System }}{{ .System }}{{ end }}\n\n\n{{ if .Prompt }}### 動態上下文\n{{ .Prompt }}\n{{ end }}\n\n### 輸出（純 JSON，無其他）\n\"\"\"\n```\n\nThe problem is likely that the template structure is causing the model to expect input in a specific format that isn't being provided correctly. With ray-v1 working but ray-v3 timing out, the template might be leaving the model waiting for something, or the system prompt isn't being injected properly into the template context. the model to behave incorrectly.\n\nLooking at the Modelfile again:\n- The SYSTEM prompt is long (contains all the master alignment logic)\n- The TEMPLATE is: `{{ if .System }}{{ .System }}{{ end }}{{ if .Prompt }}### 動態上下文\\n{{ .Prompt }}\\n{{ end }}\\n\\n### 輸出（純 JSON，無其他）\\n`\n\nWhen I send messages via API with `messages: [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"...\"}]`, Ollama renders the template differently depending on whether it's using the chat endpoint or generate endpoint. With the chat endpoint and my Modelfile, the model might be getting confused about whether it's a system message or user message.\n\nThe TIMEOUT issue is likely the culprit - 22 seconds suggests the model is generating but hitting the default `num_predict` limit and timing out. My Modelfile does set `PARAMETER num_predict 512`, which should be sufficient, but maybe the temperature or other parameters are causing it to generate longer than expected. Let me try bypassing the Modelfile entirely and hitting the qwen3.5:4b base model directly to see if that's the bottleneck.","thinkingSignature":"d6cd110bd0d8ea3c0119b61a9d85f68a0968d7f2f4924f9d613a9deebded49a5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_isuu3e5mk9w0_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_qwen35_direct.py","content":"\"\"\"Test Ollama API directly with qwen3.5:4b (bypassing Modelfile)\"\"\"\nimport urllib.request, json, time\n\n# Test directly with the base model qwen3.5:4b\npayload = {\n    \"model\": \"qwen3.5:4b\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Say 'test' in one word only.\"}],\n    \"stream\": False,\n    \"options\": {\"temperature\": 0.1, \"num_predict\": 50}\n}\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    \"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\",\n    data=json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\"),\n    headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    method=\"POST\"\n)\nprint(\"Testing qwen3.5:4b base model...\")\nstart = time.time()\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n        raw = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n        content = raw.get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n        print(f\"qwen3.5:4b OK ({time.time()-start:.1f}s): '{content}'\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"qwen3.5:4b FAIL after {time.time()-start:.1f}s: {e}\")\n\n# Test ray-v3 with num_predict limit\npayload2 = {\n    \"model\": \"ray-v3\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Say 'test' in one word only.\"}],\n    \"stream\": False,\n    \"options\": {\"temperature\": 0.1, \"num_predict\": 20}\n}\nreq2 = urllib.request.Request(\n    \"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\",\n    data=json.dumps(payload2).encode(\"utf-8\"),\n    headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    method=\"POST\"\n)\nprint(\"\\nTesting ray-v3 with num_predict=20...\")\nstart = time.time()\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req2, timeout=30) as resp:\n        raw = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n        content = raw.get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n        print(f\"ray-v3 OK ({time.time()-start:.1f}s): '{content}'\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"ray-v3 FAIL after {time.time()-start:.1f}s: {e}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55553,"output":1051,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72353,"cost":{"input":0.0166659,"output":0.0012611999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0009449399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01887204}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778590922465,"responseId":"065257e3eab930287118a057825ec0e7"}}
