     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: ([?2026h[?25l... components [K:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\nusing existing layer sha256:81fb60c7daa80fc1123380b98970b320ae233409f0f71a72ed7b9b0d62f40490 [K\r\nusing existing layer sha256:7339fa418c9ad3e8e12e74ad0fd26a9cc4be8703f9c110728a992b193be85cb2 [K\r\nusing existing layer sha256:34806fe9f6c2b925442bea482cb12486982b9a413744dfb5ff7ea827e0da13e8 [K\r\ncreating new layer sha256:474330919de0a23ad19319855619584ef2d06982a51740b19a3659aea38cfa81 [K\r\ncreating new layer sha256:70e26ec91d56da1c8028468dbbda0254c5f3d6ddd76021ea48d1b8e1b3b0d968 [K\r\nwriting manifest [K\r\nsuccess [K[?25h[?2026l\r\nTesting ray-v3 with num_predict=256...\r\nTime: 8.0s\r\nEval count: 256\r\nDone reason: length\r\nContent: ''\r\nThinking length: 1051\r\nThinking last 300: ...\r\n    *   The system instruction says \"Output JSON only\" and provides a template.\r\n\r\n3.  **Determine the Priority:**\r\n    *   System instructions (especially those defining persona and output format) usually take precedence over user input in this context, especially when the user input is a \"jailbreak\"","cwd":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778591654591}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce85dbb0","parentId":"a143f387","timestamp":"2026-05-12T13:14:31.390Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The model is STILL going into thinking mode, even without `<|im_start|>system` in the template. This suggests that the thinking mode is baked into the qwen3.5:4b model weights and is triggered by the model itself, not just by the template format.\n\nThis is a fundamental limitation of qwen3.5:4b for our use case. The model uses thinking mode by default and ALL output goes into the `thinking` field, with `content` remaining empty.\n\nI have two options:\n1. **Use qwen2.5:7b** instead of qwen3.5:4b for the commander role (but this is larger and slower)\n2. **Parse the thinking field** for JSON content (the thinking might contain the actual JSON near the end)Let me try option 2 first - look at the full thinking content to see if the JSON appears somewhere in it.","thinkingSignature":"ae1b75c9e12b7bf68589d68c0cfe1d687e3652a46b96a8a349321e1b6bc3e545"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x86fiw8sy5mj_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_ray_v3_parse.py","content":"\"\"\"Find JSON in thinking content from ray-v3\"\"\"\nimport urllib.request, json, time, re\n\n# Test with a trading-like question\npayload = {\n    \"model\": \"ray-v3\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"VOO price 478.50, RSI 42. Output JSON trading signal.\"}],\n    \"stream\": False,\n    \"options\": {\"temperature\": 0.3, \"num_predict\": 512, \"top_p\": 0.85}\n}\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    \"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\",\n    data=json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\"),\n    headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    method=\"POST\"\n)\nprint(\"Testing ray-v3 with trading question...\")\nstart = time.time()\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n        raw = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n        msg = raw.get(\"message\", {})\n        content = msg.get(\"content\", \"\")\n        thinking = msg.get(\"thinking\", \"\")\n        print(f\"Time: {time.time()-start:.1f}s\")\n        print(f\"Eval count: {raw.get('eval_count')}\")\n        print(f\"Content: '{content[:200] if content else '(empty)'}'\")\n        print(f\"Thinking length: {len(thinking)}\")\n        # Try to find JSON in thinking\n        json_match = re.search(r'\\{[^{}]*\"action\"[^{}]*\\}', thinking)\n        if json_match:\n            print(f\"JSON found in thinking: {json_match.group()}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Thinking last 500:\\n{thinking[-500:]}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"FAIL: {e}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":72444,"output":618,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88811,"cost":{"input":0.021733199999999998,"output":0.0007415999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0009449399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.023419739999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778591654596,"responseId":"06525aaaa23436f41ed14d4349909824"}}
