{"type":"message","id":"43f34b58","parentId":"c17c5c2d","timestamp":"2026-05-12T13:17:50.170Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! `ray-deep-v1` works and returns content, but it's returning its OLD Modelfile output format (with \"diagnosis\" and \"corrected_axiom\" fields). The ray-deep-v1 has a different system prompt from when it was originally created, and it seems to still be using that.\n\nThe issue is that when I call `router._ollama_raw(model=router.local_deep, prompt=prompt, ...)`, it sends `{\"model\": \"ray-deep-v1\", \"prompt\": \"...\"}`. But the ray-deep-v1 was created with a Modelfile that uses `TEMPLATE` and `SYSTEM`, and when we send `prompt` instead of `messages`, Ollama might be handling it differently.\n\n\nI need to trace through what's happening—the model works in isolation but returns empty when called through the router's `_ollama_raw`, which suggests the issue is in how that method formats the request. Let me check the actual payload structure it's sending.\n\nLooking at the `_ollama_raw` code, I'm using the `prompt` field for ray-deep-v1, but the model might actually expect `messages` format instead—that could explain why the output is garbled or incomplete. The response is truncated JSON with \"Command understood but not relevant\" - it seems the system prompt from the original Modelfile is overriding the user prompt, likely because the template structure with `<|im_start|>` tokens is causing the model to ignore the actual prompt content.\n\nLooking at how `ollama show` displays the Modelfile, I realize that even when I send `{\"prompt\": \"...\"}` instead of `{\"messages\": [...]}`, the model still applies its baked-in SYSTEM template with the full Simons/Connors/Taleb/Thorp system prompt. That's why the short test message got interpreted through that full system context instead of just outputting the word \"test\" as intended.\n\nThe 8.2 second response time confirms the model is actually doing work - it's processing the extensive system prompt plus the short input. For the v3_commander test with a 704-character prompt, ray-deep-v1 returns empty content, which suggests the response might be getting truncated or the output format isn't what I'm expecting.\n\nLooking at the direct test with ray-deep-v1, I'm getting valid JSON output about diagnosis and corrected axioms, so the model is functional. The problem seems to be in how `_ollama_raw` handles the response or how the prompt gets formatted when it goes through that method.\n\nWhen I send `{\"prompt\": \"...\"}` directly to `/api/chat`, Ollama wraps it as a user message within the Modelfile's template structure. But if the Modelfile doesn't have an `<|im_start|>assistant` marker, the model might just output nothing since it's waiting for that final token to start generating. I should try switching to `messages` format instead to see if that gives me better control over the generation.","thinkingSignature":"ef09f6f5d26bfb0f67ed30f06671d55fd187792cde8aef4d480bf8f908d33942"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0n6ey4snoh33_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_raydeep_messages.py","content":"\"\"\"Test ray-deep-v1 with messages format\"\"\"\nimport urllib.request, json, time\n\n# Try with messages format (like ray-v1 works)\npayload = {\n    \"model\": \"ray-deep-v1\",\n    \"messages\": [\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Say 'test' in one word only. No explanation.\"}\n    ],\n    \"stream\": False,\n    \"options\": {\"temperature\": 0.1, \"num_predict\": 20}\n}\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    \"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\",\n    data=json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\"),\n    headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    method=\"POST\"\n)\nprint(\"Testing ray-deep-v1 with messages...\")\nstart = time.time()\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as resp:\n        raw = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n        content = raw.get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n        print(f\"OK ({time.time()-start:.1f}s): '{content}'\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"FAIL: {e}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":77073,"output":895,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93717,"cost":{"input":0.023121899999999997,"output":0.0010739999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0009449399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025140839999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778591844763,"responseId":"06525b68cc0b5e108687b93190be6ec8"}}
