{"type":"message","id":"451c3ea0","parentId":"307073a0","timestamp":"2026-05-12T13:23:34.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The v3_commander is working now but the output is still using the old format (`diagnosis`, `corrected_axiom`) instead of the new commander format (`action`, `confidence`, `logic_bridge`). This is because the ray-commander model was built on top of ray-deep-v1 which has the old system prompt baked into its weights.\n\nThe issue is that when I use `FROM ray-deep-v1:latest`, it copies the SYSTEM prompt from ray-deep-v1's Modelfile (which has the old Simons/Taleb/Thorp prompts), not the new one I specified in my Modelfile's SYSTEM section.\n\nActually wait - that's not how Ollama works. When you use `FROM ray-deep-v1:latest`, it uses the base model weights (qwen2.5:7b) and then applies your new SYSTEM prompt. The new SYSTEM prompt should override the old one.\n\n\nBut the test output shows the old format, which means the SYSTEM prompt in my Modelfile isn't being applied. Looking at the raw output, there's a `{\"diagnosis\":...}` block that matches the old ray-deep-v1 Modelfile's JSON schema, not the new commander schema I defined. Something's not overriding correctly.\n\nWait - I see the issue now. When I tested with `router.local_deep`, it was still using the old model instead of ray-commander. The SYSTEM prompt should take precedence when explicitly defined, but it seems like the old system prompt from ray-deep-v1 is still being used somehow. Let me verify what model the test is actually calling. The model is returning the old JSON schema instead of the new one I defined in ray-commander's system prompt. The output contains `{\"diagnosis\":...}` when it should have `{\"strategy_name\":..., \"action\":..., \"confidence\":...}`. This suggests the SYSTEM prompt from ray-deep-v1 might still be taking precedence, or my Modelfile's system prompt didn't apply correctly when I built ray-commander from ray-deep-v1. Let me test the ray-commander model directly to see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"781d2df6541098079dae018df20cbcb32d7183933c25973ce4e6bc001993c344"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ya2diunwpgot_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_commander_direct.py","content":"\"\"\"Test ray-commander directly\"\"\"\nimport urllib.request, json, time\n\npayload = {\n    \"model\": \"ray-commander\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"VOO price 478.50, RSI 42. Output trading signal JSON.\"}],\n    \"stream\": False,\n    \"options\": {\"temperature\": 0.3, \"num_predict\": 300}\n}\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    \"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\",\n    data=json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\"),\n    headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    method=\"POST\"\n)\nprint(\"Testing ray-commander...\")\nstart = time.time()\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as resp:\n        raw = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n        content = raw.get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n        print(f\"OK ({time.time()-start:.1f}s)\")\n        print(f\"Content ({len(content)} chars): {content[:300]}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"FAIL: {e}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83933,"output":717,"cacheRead":15749,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100399,"cost":{"input":0.025179899999999998,"output":0.0008604,"cacheRead":0.0009449399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.026985239999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778592194984,"responseId":"06525cc6885469105f443e4b512321d8"}}
